This paper is primarily focused on the detection and prevention of cyber-attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed system utilizes machine learning techniques to predict the likelihood of future attacks, which suggests a strong connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The system also takes into account network entities, such as IP addresses, which suggests a connection to network infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the system, such as alert prioritization and blacklist assembly, which suggests a connection to systems and information theory (cs.SI).
